Meanwhile of course , your typical American boy racer (like DeMuro) doesn't give a fuck about climate change and/or global warming and/or  excessive vehicle emissions. snippet.textDisplay: The 2005 to 2010 Dodge Charger used the LX platform. From 2011 on up - it used [and continues to use] the LD platform - which is, "an entirely redesigned and updated platform but is closely related to the original LX." It's NOT the same thing. Tom McCarthy - the Chrysler 300's CHIEF ENGINEER - said the 2011 300 and Charger have a new rear suspension, steering column, seat frames, wiring harnesses and switches. The list goes on. Even the chassis is new. "I think a lot of people just assumed it was a carryover chassis from the previous car," he said. "It is not. It is all new."
